The paper focuses on the effects of visual stimuli on the performance of security-critical tasks, which involves human-computer interaction (HCI) and cybersecurity (CR). The study also involves the use of automated experimental environments, which falls under the category of cybernetics (CY), systems and control (SI), and software engineering (SE).
